	<transcript sound="sound1"><![CDATA[Pests seek entry to food premises for their basic needs like food and shelter.<br /><br />Food premises attract pests because they provide ideal living conditions for them to survive and multiply.<br /><br />Most premises provide:<li>Food;</li><li>Warmth;</li><li>Harbourage;</li><li>Moisture; and</li><li>Security.</li><br />Several common pests thrive in small, dark, undisturbed spaces.<br /><br />Most pests are attracted by debris from human activities.<br /><br />Raw materials, including packaging and laundry, may bring pests into the premises, so susceptible products should be carefully checked before transferring to storage.]]></transcript>

		
	
